topicID=1759.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Older Topic: Lodi&amp;rbb vs. cof</span><hr size=1> RBB 31% , CoF 36% .  Shisshar ( assuming what you get on raids/groups) 66%, and haste cap w/o bard song is 100%?<br><br>31 + 66 = 97 ( RBB )<br>36+ 66 = 100 [ minus 2 due to cap ] (CoF)<br><br>so what you are comparing is<br><br>3% haste 19agi 4dex  30hp ( CoF / Spider )<br><br>vs.<br><br>20str 10sta 3ac 20fr 20cr 10mr : Enduring Breath ( RBB / Lodi )<br><br><br>i think i am right here, but maybe not. Feel Free to correct me.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br> <p><a href= http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55375>Trakceles Mcmarrin</a><BR>60th Warlord<BR><a href= "http://theshadoworder.com">The Shadow Order</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uturomtoesmasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Turom Toesmasher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 9:34:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1759.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Older Topic: Lodi&amp;rbb vs. cof</span><hr size=1> Just two points I'd like to make:<br><br>1) I don't have a chanter in my back pocket, so I don't always have 66% spell haste on me.  Sometimes my only spell haste is from a Shaman.<br><br>2) I've heard 100% and 105% is the max for haste, I really don't know which one is true.  I'd personally rather have as much taunt as possible, in every situation.  When I'm MT, I hit disarm constantly.  Does this add a lot of taunt?  No, probably not, but IMHO ever little bit counts.  In this case, I've always decided to opt for the 3-5% increase in haste. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11741 target="magelo">Turom Toesmasher</a><br>57 Myrmidon<br>The Seventh Hammer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaricgranath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aric Granath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 9:28:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1759.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Older Topic: Lodi&amp;rbb vs. cof</span><hr size=1> If you want to do the Lodi / RBB combo (which I was contemplating on doing), change the RBB to a Spiked Seahorse Hide Belt (34% haste)... then you are only losing 2% haste, which in my opinion, is very neglible. <p>-----------------------------------<BR>Aric Granath<BR>-- <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=37456">Zerapheus al'Einherjar</a>, Barbarian Myrmidion<BR>-- <A HREF="http://www.dvdprofiler.com/mycollection.asp?alias=AricGranath">DVD Lewtz!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhellra1ser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HELLRA1SER</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/02 1:48:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1759.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hellra1ser.homestead.com/files/SelfPortraits/HELLRA1SER.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Older Topic: Lodi&amp;rbb vs. cof</span><hr size=1> Yea, I'd go with the Spiked Belt instead of RBB if you decided to take the deal.  I had the Lodizal Shell Shield and RBB combo on my Warrior.  I figured the differences with the Seahorse Hide Cloak and RBB vs. CoF and Spid Fur Belt (what I had available at the time) when someone offered to trade their CoF for my RBB+ and chose to stick with the RBB, since I didn't want to pay more to get almost no difference.<br><br>I liked my Lodizal for the resists, EB, and the light it gives off.  It helped my blind Barbarian eyes.  The RBB was sort of affordable for me.  It's basically 2x the going rate of a RBG on the Innoruuk server.  The CoF goes for significantly more.  Your deal sounds about even, value wise.  Though, it wouldn't make me move to Lod/RBB if I had to spend the 20k I was saving up.<br><br>There would be almost no difference in haste cap if you went with the Seahorse Spiked Belt in places where taunt would be important.  In those events, you would definitely have an enchanter with you.<br><br>The difference when soloing would be about even.  If you were soloing mushrooms in FG, if thier procs save vs. magic (like all other stuns and almost all slows; Gorenaire, Emerald Drake, and 1 new luclin shaman slow are the only ones I can think of and they have different icons), then the Lodizal will help.  More AC when soloing in Velk's.  Soloing in the Grey... etc.<br><br>Bottom line is, you're going to spend 20k (or more for the Seahorse Belt) for only a few small differences.  Extra trouble which you don't need.  I'd keep the CoF unless you get an exceptional deal. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhellra1ser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HELLRA1SER</A> at: 2/9/02 2:02:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uxantheusdiabolus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xantheus Diab